The `RootLayout.tsx` file defines the main structure and global styles for the entire DocMed application. It sets up the necessary providers, fonts, and metadata for the Next.js application.

### Purpose

- Establishes the fundamental HTML structure of the application.
- Integrates Clerk authentication provider for user management.
- Applies global CSS styles and custom fonts (Geist Sans and Geist Mono).
- Defines the application's metadata (title and description).

### Key Exports/Functions/Props

- **`metadata`**: An object containing metadata for the application, including `title` and `description`.
- **`RootLayout`**: The default export, a React functional component that serves as the root layout. It accepts `children` as a prop, which represents the content of the current page or nested layout.

### Usage Example

This file is automatically used by Next.js as the main layout. All pages within the `app` directory will be wrapped by this layout. The `children` prop dynamically renders the content of each specific page. For instance, a page located at `app/page.tsx` would have its content rendered within the `<body>` tags defined in this layout.

```tsx
// Example of how this layout wraps a page's content

// app/layout.tsx
// ... (layout definition as above)

// app/page.tsx
// export default function HomePage() {
//   return (
//     <main>
//       <h1>Welcome to DocMed</h1>
//     </main>
//   );
// }

// When HomePage is rendered, it will be inside the structure defined in layout.tsx
```
